timezone() - Method in class org.apache.arrow.flatbuf.Timestamp
The time zone is a string indicating the name of a time zone, one of: * As used in the Olson time zone database (the "tz database" or "tzdata"), such as "America/New_York" * An absolute time zone offset of the form +XX:XX or -XX:XX, such as +07:30 Whether a timezone string is present indicates different semantics about the data: * If the time zone is null or equal to an empty string, the data is "time zone naive" and shall be displayed *as is* to the user, not localized to the locale of the user.
